AB  - The portfolio balance channel for sterilised intervention is tested by examining the effects of changes in relative asset supplies on the dollar-Deutschemark rate during the 1980s. In contrast to previous studies, we control for any signalling effects of central bank intervention and find a weak, but statistically significant, portfolio balance influence on the exchange rate.
